[1] North Carolina, rabid fox
Date: 6 Jul 2010
Source: Wake MyNC.com [edited]
<http://wake.mync.com/site/wake/news/story/53332/rabies-case-confirmed-in-wake-forest>


A rabies notice has been issued for residents near Stony Hill Road in
Wake Forest, NC. Wake County health officials say a case of rabies
was confirmed on 6 Jul 2010 in a fox near Rivermead Lane and Stonewyck Lane.

"We don't want to alarm residents in the Wake Forest and North
Raleigh areas, but they should be aware of this case and of the
potential for exposure to themselves, family members and their pets,"
said Michael Williams, Animal Control director for Wake County.

