[3] Connecticut, rabid bobcat
Date: 6 Jul 2010
Source: The Courant [edited]
<http://www.courant.com/community/simsbury/hc-simsbury-bobcat-attack-0706-20100705,0,821917.story>


A bobcat that attacked 2 dogs and scratched a person trying to rescue
the dogs has tested positive for rabies, police said.

The attack occurred about 6:30 p.m. Saturday [3 Jul 2010] at a home
on Terry's Plain Road. Police said a resident, whose identity was not
available, told them that a bobcat attacked his 2 dogs.

One person was scratched by the bobcat while trying to get the 2 dogs
away from it. The homeowner was able to subdue the bobcat and hold it
in a small cage until police arrived.

The animal was taken to the state lab for testing on and on Monday [5
Jul 2010] police learned that the bobcat was rabid, said Sgt. James
White. The dogs were up to date with rabies vaccinations and the
person exposed to the bobcat will seek treatment, White said.

